choices.text:
what are the verb tenses?
There are several verb tenses in English grammar, including: 
1. Present Tense (I walk)
2. Past Tense (I walked)
3. Future Tense (I will walk)
4. Simple Past Tense (I had walked)
5. Continuous Tense (I am walking)
6. Perfect Tense (I have walked)
7. Pluperfect Tense (I had been walking) 
Verb tenses indicate the time frame of an action or state, whether it is happening now, happened in the past, will happen in the future, etc.
